 <text id="A0814T">
  <front id="d2">
   <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
    <p>Harman writes to his Uncle Albert to tell him about rumors of Thomas Garber's death.</p>
   </div1>
  </front>
  <body id="d4">
   <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
    <opener>
     <pb n="1" entity="garb14" pid="uva-lib:503051"/>
    

     <name type="recipient">Albert Garber</name>
     <dateline>
      <date value="1863-06-20">June 20, 1863</date>
      <name type="place">Staunton</name>
     </dateline>
     <salute>Dear Uncle,</salute>
    </opener>

    <p> I have just Heard Maj T.P. Eskridge told Mr. B. Evans that Tom was killed &amp; his body
     left on the Field. I have been down to see Col Davidson &amp; Bill but can hear <hi
      rend="underline">nothing</hi>. I Hope it is untrue. Come in before you say anything to Aunt or
     the Family about it.</p>

    <closer>
     <salute>Truly your nephew</salute>
     <signed>MG Harman</signed>
    </closer>
   </div1>
  </body>
 </text>
